 1. Use modern c++20 constructs when writing code
 2. Follow the cpp core guidelines
 3. Use braced initialization {} over copy initialization (=) or parentheses ()
 4. Follow good OOP design principles
 5. Make the code self-documenting through proper naming of variables - never include inline comments in implementations
 6. Classes should be structured as follows:
Static members
Public functions
Protected functions
Private functions
Public members
Protected members
Private members
7. Use "_" as a prefix for instance variables
